        "committer": {
          "name": "Chris Horn",
          "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix setting transaction nob",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix setting transaction nob\n\nThe kfilnd transaction number of bytes is suppose to be the LNet\npayload byte count. But, the tn_nob field was not being set for all\noperations in addition to being set incorrectly. The end result of\nthis bug is the mlength being reported in LNet reply events was\nincorrect. This prevented Lustre from running.\n\nCorrectly set tn_nob to the LNet payload size. In addition, report a\nmlength of zero for LNet reply events if an error has occurred during\nthe transaction.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9931\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: Iaba794d9105827ffa3fc2d1e0be989b49fcd1ded\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
